<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870112-0028 </DOCNO><HL> McDonnell GetsWork From U.S.For $201.8 Million</HL><DD> 01/12/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> LIT LTV MD GE UTX HONAEROSPACE (ARO)DEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF) </IN><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   McDonnell Douglas Corp. received contracts totaling $201.8 million for F-15 aircraft production and C17 aircraft development for the Air Force and for production of assault weapons for the Army.    Sikorsky Aircraft, a unit of United Technologies Corp., was awarded a $101.4 million Army contract for UH-60 helicopters.    Central Gulf Mines Inc. won Navy contracts totaling $81.7 million for ship charters.    General Electric Co. received contracts totaling $66.8 million for helicopter engines, radio equipment and aircraft engine parts for the Navy, projectile technology development for the Army and satellite modifications for the Air Force.    LTV Corp. was issued $37.5 million in contracts for telemetry equipment for the Navy and projectile technology development for the Army.    Litton Industries Inc. was awarded Air Force contracts totaling $33.8 million for production and modification of navigation equipment.    Honeywell Inc. received a $29.9 million Army contract for tank ammunition. </TEXT></DOC>